@@dNIGHTBLADE@@W

Born where moonlight fails and steel whispers, Nightblades are the perfected
fusion of @@dAssassin@@W precision and @@dWarlock@@W cruelty. They are not mere
killers; they are executioners of the unseen hour, striking from angles most
foes never learn to fear until it is too late.

To become a Nightblade, you must master either @@dAssassin@@W or @@dWarlock@@W
(remort prerequisites for the adept path).

@@dPassive class advantages@@W
Nightblade grants several always-on combat bonuses as your adept level rises:

  1) @@wCritical chance bonus@@W
     - You gain passive critical-hit chance from Nightblade level.
     - Scaling: +0.25% crit chance per Nightblade level (up to +5% at 20).

  2) @@wCritical damage bonus@@W
     - Your critical strikes deal more damage.
     - Scaling: +0.5% crit multiplier per Nightblade level (up to +10% at 20).

  3) @@wBackstab / circle damage bonus@@W
     - Backstab and circle gain a direct Nightblade damage multiplier.
     - Scaling: +2% damage per Nightblade level (up to +40% at 20).

  4) @@wExtra attack round@@W
     - Having any Nightblade adept level grants an additional melee hit in the
       multi-hit calculation.

@@dUnique Nightblade mechanics@@W
  * @@wNightblade stance@@W becomes available, including the @@ddual backstab@@W
    stance flag for high-pressure opener play.
  * @@wPoison:nightshade@@W is learned at Nightblade level 2.
  * Nightblade uses @@wDexterity@@W as its adept prime attribute and follows the
    adept progression profile for survivability and mana growth.

@@dNightblade reincarnation bonus@@W
Each Nightblade adept reincarnation grants an additional passive bonus:

  * @@wBackstab / circle damage@@W: +2% per Nightblade adept reincarnation.
    This stacks with the normal Nightblade adept level scaling above.

In short: Nightblade is the apex stealth-damage adept, specializing in
critical lethality and empowered backstab/circle kill windows.

See also: @@mremort assassinate backstab circle poison:nightshade stance@@W
